snippet.textDisplay:
OK...Love it. BUT....with how you have to turn slightly off the tail end, I'm predicting right now that with just a LITTLE bit of moisture on your tires, even if the wood isn't wet, someone is going to sllp right off the end and have a bad ending. My suggestion....add a little bit of rise on the outside of the take off end so that it's "hipped" slightly to the right, so that you have more tread on it to prevent slippage. Other than that...looks like a blast! Also...making the berm bigget going into "Kevin's Jump" was a no brainer to make the line more doable for most riders. It takes a lot of trust to throw your bike into berms that short and trust that your tires are going to hook up.

Great work guys....looking forward to more build projects!!
